&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to be part of an amazing team who provide high quality and safe care, striving towards excellence? University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire are looking for motivated and enthusiastic Midwives to join our Maternity team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a newly qualified Band 5 or an experienced Band 6 who would like to make a difference to women and their families, then we would like to hear from you. University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire Maternity department are forward thinking and innovative trust. There are many opportunities available to enhance and progress in your career including being part of the Complex Care Team, Enhanced Maternity Care Team, and Continuity Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Continuity of Carer model has been successfully introduced throughout pregnancy, labour and the postnatal period which supports the Better Births vision. Successful candidates have the opportunity to work in both the hospital and community setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time and part time hours are available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like any further information, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sharon Gouldingay Modern Matron for Inpatient Services either by telephone 02476966573 or email: Sharon.gouldingay@uhcw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
